structure and function of the coronary microcirculation resulting in an inadequate coronary blood supply is deÔ¨Åned as CMD.
MOLECULAR MECHANISMS. Although the mechanisms leading to CMD are not entirely clear, oxidative stress, caused by cellular reactive oxygen species (ROS) overproduction and accumulation together with the consequent inÔ¨Çammatory response, are considered key pathogenic mechanisms driving the development of CMD (6). Endothelial cells play a crucial role in regulating vasomotor activity by releasing vasoactive substances such as vasodilator nitric oxide (NO) and vasoconstrictor endothelin (ET)-1. Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate oxidases

